1
00:00:03,987 --> 00:00:06,695
What's expressed from the heart of the devotee,

2
00:00:06,695 --> 00:00:08,336
so what's coming out of the heart

3
00:00:08,336 --> 00:00:12,820
of Jayadev Goswami, expressed in the Gita Govinda,

4
00:00:13,758 --> 00:00:18,060
that's giving great joy to Chaitanya Mahaprabhu.

5
00:00:18,060 --> 00:00:21,980
[The Givers of Inaccessible]

6
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:26,101
So we can't think "Well it's kind of an esoteric point.

7
00:00:26,101 --> 00:00:27,302
How is this practical?

8
00:00:27,302 --> 00:00:28,940
What about the guy on the bus?

9
00:00:28,940 --> 00:00:30,501
The guy in the tuk-tuk?

10
00:00:30,501 --> 00:00:32,981
What is he going to do with this?"

11
00:00:32,981 --> 00:00:35,272
Well, not everything is meant to please

12
00:00:35,272 --> 00:00:38,977
the guy in the tuk-tuk, or the guy in the bus.

13
00:00:41,053 --> 00:00:46,382
They're writing things that please Chaitanya Maharaprabhu.

14
00:00:47,227 --> 00:00:52,221
yā niśā sarva-bhūtānāṁ tasyāṁ jāgarti saṁyamī [BG 2.69]

15
00:00:52,221 --> 00:00:56,982
What's in the mind of Einstein and Heisenberg

16
00:00:56,982 --> 00:01:02,251
and the quark guy, Planck,

17
00:01:03,128 --> 00:01:06,119
that's madness to ordinary people.

18
00:01:06,119 --> 00:01:08,035
But is it madness?

19
00:01:08,035 --> 00:01:10,140
It's madness to ordinary people,

20
00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:11,873
but is it, there's nothing there?

21
00:01:11,873 --> 00:01:15,274
Or there's something very powerful and substantial there?

22
00:01:15,274 --> 00:01:19,887
So what's being expressed in this sort of love poetry,

23
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:23,741
yes, it's very high and very wonderful,

24
00:01:23,741 --> 00:01:26,300
but that's what Krishna consciousness is,

25
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:28,951
it's something very high and very wonderful.

26
00:01:29,843 --> 00:01:36,187
Yes, our general position is to provide things

27
00:01:36,187 --> 00:01:39,341
that are accessible, but at the same time,

28
00:01:39,341 --> 00:01:42,220
it's giving accessibility to something

29
00:01:42,220 --> 00:01:45,355
that's ultimately very high and wonderful.

30
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:48,782
As Guru Maharaj said, the most exclusive

31
00:01:48,782 --> 00:01:52,852
but the means to achieve it will be all-inclusive.

32
00:01:52,852 --> 00:01:56,182
So we're in the all-inclusive mode,

33
00:01:56,182 --> 00:01:58,623
then we'll figure out different ways of accessibility.

34
00:01:58,623 --> 00:02:03,060
But it's to bring people to that most exclusive plain.

35
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:05,522
Where? What is its characteristic?

36
00:02:05,522 --> 00:02:08,420
Sri Krishna karshini ca sa,

37
00:02:08,420 --> 00:02:12,021
Krishna's so charmed by the devotion

38
00:02:12,021 --> 00:02:13,862
in the heart of the devotee,

39
00:02:13,862 --> 00:02:17,782
that great infinite magnitude sun we're talking about,

40
00:02:17,782 --> 00:02:22,207
comes under the control of the ray, the finite.

41
00:02:22,854 --> 00:02:28,121
From this example, the sun comes under the control of the ray.

42
00:02:29,521 --> 00:02:31,187
How's that possible?

43
00:02:31,187 --> 00:02:34,103
Because what's in the heart, love and affection,

44
00:02:34,103 --> 00:02:35,940
is so valuable, as Guru Maharaj said,

45
00:02:35,940 --> 00:02:40,380
love's the greatest thing ever invented. (As if it was invented.)

46
00:02:40,841 --> 00:02:43,216
That... Krishna's so eager for that,

47
00:02:43,216 --> 00:02:47,261
he comes under the control of the devotee.

48
00:02:47,813 --> 00:02:50,081
That's the extra-ordinary thing.

49
00:02:51,388 --> 00:02:52,965
Hare Krishna

